Universalsprache an: "And being the only speech that is natural to man, it [the hand, C.M.] may

weil be called the tongue and generallanguage of human nature which, without teaching, men in

all regions of the habitable world do at the first sight most easily understand. This is evident by

that trade and commerce with those salvage nations who have long enjoyed the late discovered

